" Pressing `j` and `k` really do move you to the next or prev lines
nnoremap j gj
nnoremap k gk

" Make sure I don't enter that bullshit ex mode
nnoremap Q <Nop>

" Force myself to not use the arrow keys
ino <left>  <Nop>
ino <down>  <Nop>
ino <up>    <Nop>
ino <right> <nop>

" And in visual mode ...
vno <left>  <Nop>
vno <down>  <Nop>
vno <up>    <Nop>
vno <right> <Nop>

" And even in normal mode
no <left>  <Nop>
no <down>  <Nop>
no <up>    <Nop>
no <right> <Nop>

" Make tab navigation work like sublime
nnoremap <C-t> :tabnew<CR>
nnoremap <C-w> :tabclose<CR>
nnoremap <C-]> :tabnext<CR>
nnoremap <C-[> :tabprevious<CR>
inoremap <C-t> <Esc>:tabnew<CR>
inoremap <C-w> <Esc>:tabclose<CR>
inoremap <C-]> <Esc>:tabnext<CR>i
inoremap <C-[> <Esc>:tabprevious<CR>i
